WEBVTT

00:00.901 --> 00:03.604
My name is Earl.

00:03.671 --> 00:06.440
[ Earl Narrating ]
Havin' a baby can be
very hard on a woman.

00:06.507 --> 00:10.478
And because of that,
it can be hard on the man too.

00:10.544 --> 00:14.548
Darnell, you are gonna have to
pick the kids up from school.

00:14.615 --> 00:18.386
Baby, I'm tryin' to pick
all the broken lightbulb
out of the gumbo.

00:18.452 --> 00:22.890
- Why can't you do it?
- I am growin' a human being
in my body cell by cell.

00:22.956 --> 00:26.294
I need my rest, Darnell.
My stomach could be buildin'
its brain today. You don't know.

00:26.360 --> 00:28.929
[ Earl Narrating ]
Watching Joy being pregnant...

00:28.996 --> 00:31.432
reminded me of somethin' I
should've done a long time ago--

00:31.499 --> 00:35.035
finish makin' a lamp
I started in eighth grade
industrial arts class.

00:35.103 --> 00:38.339
I don't remember which wire
I'm supposed to hook
to the yellow wire.

00:38.406 --> 00:42.343
Come on, Earl. Hurry up.
I need to plug the TV back
into the electricity holes.

00:42.410 --> 00:44.578
Cannonball Run 2
is startin' on Channel 5.

00:44.645 --> 00:47.848
And you know
if I miss the beginning,
I get lost in the story.

00:47.915 --> 00:50.718
The teacher had
some sort of rhyme.

00:50.784 --> 00:53.521
Red you're dead.

00:53.587 --> 00:56.157
Maybe "bluey"
goes "kapluey."

00:56.224 --> 00:59.693
Earl, we're runnin'
out of time.

00:59.760 --> 01:01.895
Fine. I'll just guess.

01:01.962 --> 01:04.064
Here goes nothin'.

01:06.400 --> 01:08.802
I guess it's all right.

01:08.869 --> 01:13.107
Wait a second. I think
this is last month's TV Guide.

01:13.174 --> 01:15.576
[ Electricity Crackling ]

01:15.643 --> 01:19.647
[ Earl Narrating ] So what does
Joy bein' pregnant have to do
with me finishin' this lamp?

01:19.713 --> 01:21.515
Well, that's a long story.

01:21.582 --> 01:24.285
Now, most people
already know me and Joy met...

01:24.352 --> 01:26.787
and got married
under unusual circumstances.

01:26.854 --> 01:30.191
I was drunk,
and she was pregnant
with someone else's child.

01:30.258 --> 01:32.326
But I loved her nonetheless.

01:32.393 --> 01:35.095
I can't say my new wife and my
parents hit it off right away,

01:35.163 --> 01:38.332
but Joy wasn't the first
thing I did my parents
didn't approve of.

01:38.399 --> 01:41.335
So, who is the father?

01:41.402 --> 01:44.572
Oh, I didn't get a name.
You know how crazy concerts are.

01:46.974 --> 01:49.610
I'm gonna go lay down.

01:52.480 --> 01:54.448
[ Earl Narrating ]
A few months later,
Joy had the baby,

01:54.515 --> 01:58.619
and other than my parents
not volunteering to babysit,
things were workin' great.

01:58.686 --> 02:02.590
Gettin' near the road again.
[ Baby Muttering ]

02:02.656 --> 02:06.194
- ** [ Music Box ]
- [ Horn Honking ]

02:06.260 --> 02:09.463
We were
the all-American family.

02:09.530 --> 02:12.900
[ Baby Crying ]
Then, out of nowhere,
the baby started cryin'.

02:12.966 --> 02:15.068
He cried all day.

02:15.135 --> 02:17.405
[ Crying Continues ]

02:17.471 --> 02:20.140
Then he cried all night.

02:21.509 --> 02:24.212
No matter how much
two people love each other,

02:24.278 --> 02:26.814
the stresses of parenthood
can put a strain
on any relationship.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.817
- Walk him.
- Crabman just brought
my crab parts.

02:29.883 --> 02:32.786
- Walk him!
- [ Baby Continues Crying ]

02:37.691 --> 02:39.893
I swear to God if that
thing doesn't stop cryin',

02:39.960 --> 02:43.531
I'm gonna put him
in a gunnysack and smack him
up against the side of a barn.

02:43.597 --> 02:46.434
** [ Country On Jukebox ]
I'm just blowin' off steam.

02:46.500 --> 02:48.436
If you tell the cops
I said that,

02:48.502 --> 02:52.540
I swear to God I'll tie you up
behind my car and do doughnuts
in the mall parking lot.

02:52.606 --> 02:54.642
[ Earl Narrating ]
And it wasn't just Joy.

02:54.708 --> 02:57.311
I was takin' my "stressiness"
out on her too.

02:57.378 --> 02:59.447
- We're out of antifreeze!
- What?

02:59.513 --> 03:03.717
- We're out of antifreeze!
- How do you forget
to put in the antifreeze?

03:03.784 --> 03:06.620
How do I forget
to put in antifreeze?

03:06.687 --> 03:10.724
How do you forget to put a damn
diaphragm in before you go
to a Ronnie James Dio concert?

03:10.791 --> 03:12.926
[ Earl Narrating ]
Things were bad.

03:12.993 --> 03:16.163
So, like a lot of married
people do when they're going
through a rough patch,

03:16.230 --> 03:18.165
we "seeked" counseling.

03:18.232 --> 03:21.502
Raising a child is hard,
and I'm sure that everybody
in this audience would agree.

03:21.569 --> 03:25.005
The important thing is
that you gotta take breaks
every now and then for yourself.

03:25.072 --> 03:28.242
I mean, one person
should watch the baby
and give the other person...

03:28.309 --> 03:30.911
