She said she was gonna get
all white meat to make me feel
better about my situation.

15:14.181 --> 15:16.984
You can't just move back in.
We don't have the room.

15:17.050 --> 15:19.186
Where are your kids
gonna sleep?

15:19.252 --> 15:21.688
I don't have any kids.
Well, where's your wife?

15:21.754 --> 15:25.858
Still at the hospital,
probably startin' to figure out
I left her cheatin' ass.

15:25.925 --> 15:29.629
That or she's bangin'
an Asian doctor, tryin' to get
one of everything.

15:29.696 --> 15:31.931
Okay.

15:33.533 --> 15:35.435
I see.

15:35.502 --> 15:39.772
Son, I know you're upset
because he's not your kid.

15:39.839 --> 15:42.475
I was upset
he wasn't my grandson.

15:42.542 --> 15:45.478
And you've got
every right to get mad.

15:45.545 --> 15:49.816
So stay here
for a couple hours, get drunk,
punch a bunch of pillows--

15:49.882 --> 15:53.253
Your mom's got 18
of the damn things on the bed.
Take your pick.

15:53.320 --> 15:57.124
But then you gotta
do the right thing.
You gotta go back.

15:57.190 --> 15:59.459
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, right.

15:59.526 --> 16:01.961
Earl, I'm serious.

16:02.029 --> 16:04.331
I'm not gonna let you
walk away from this...

16:04.397 --> 16:07.134
like I've let you walk away
from everything else
in your life.

16:07.200 --> 16:10.070
I'm not gonna do it anymore.
When you were growing up,

16:10.137 --> 16:12.372
it was always easier
to let you quit stuff...

16:12.439 --> 16:14.541
and not force you
to stick with it.

16:14.607 --> 16:16.809
Piano lessons, baseball.

16:16.876 --> 16:19.746
You brought home that damn lamp
you were supposed to make...

16:19.812 --> 16:23.616
in eighth grade
industrial arts class, and it
doesn't even have a cord in it.

16:23.683 --> 16:25.518
It's a stump with a shade.

16:25.585 --> 16:27.620
Dad, you know I'm scared
of electricity.

16:27.687 --> 16:31.691
As your father, I should've
made you finish it,
but I didn't.

16:31.758 --> 16:35.662
I got three generations
of gerbils in there because
I let you walk away from 'em.

16:35.728 --> 16:38.898
I messed up. I'm not gonna
let that happen again.

16:38.965 --> 16:42.001
And these aren't gerbils
you're walkin' away from
this time.

16:42.069 --> 16:45.472
They're people--
people who need you.

16:47.307 --> 16:49.842
Look, I-I know
it's not gonna be easy.

16:49.909 --> 16:55.482
But I promise if you go back,
eventually you'll realize
it's the right thing to do.

16:58.351 --> 17:00.387
Nope.

17:00.453 --> 17:02.555
Excuse me?

17:02.622 --> 17:05.125
- I'm not doin' it.
- Yes, you are!

17:05.192 --> 17:07.460
- Says who?
- Says me!

17:07.527 --> 17:11.531
I'm doing what I should've done
a long time ago and forcing you
to stick with something.

17:11.598 --> 17:13.966
Now go take care
of your family.

17:14.033 --> 17:16.569
What happens if I don't?

17:16.636 --> 17:18.671
I'll do something.

17:18.738 --> 17:21.774
What? What are you
gonna do, Dad? Spank me?

17:21.841 --> 17:23.876
I'm not 17 anymore.

17:23.943 --> 17:27.614
Okay. All right.
Okay. All right.

17:27.680 --> 17:29.316
You're right.

17:30.883 --> 17:33.220
There's nothing I can do.

17:34.187 --> 17:36.423
That's right.
I'm a grown man.

17:36.489 --> 17:39.392
You don't tell me what to do.
Tucked-in shirts.

17:40.460 --> 17:43.263
Dad, what the hell
are you doin'?

17:43.330 --> 17:46.099
I'm gonna kill your gerbils!
Dad, give me my gerbils!

17:46.166 --> 17:48.701
Not until you go back
to your family.

17:48.768 --> 17:50.770
Dad, this isn't funny!

17:50.837 --> 17:53.706
I'm gonna throw 'em
out the window!
I'm not kidding!

17:56.343 --> 17:59.212
Dad, cut it out.
You're not gonna kill
the gerbils.

17:59.279 --> 18:03.683
I'm gonna do what I have to do
to get you to stick with
something for once in your life!

18:03.750 --> 18:07.454
If that means I have to smash
a few gerbils, then I'm gonna
smash a few gerbils.

18:07.520 --> 18:10.290
Fine. Throw a gerbil.
I dare you.

18:13.460 --> 18:15.528
See? I knew you wouldn't.

18:17.364 --> 18:20.333
- Son of a bitch!
- [ Gerbil Squeaking ]

18:21.534 --> 18:23.870
Dad, what the hell
are you doin'?

18:23.936 --> 18:27.207
- You gonna go take care
of your family?
- She cheated on me!

18:27.274 --> 18:30.977
Sorry, buddy.
She cheated on him.

18:31.043 --> 18:33.646
Oh, my God.
[ Grunts ]

18:37.517 --> 18:39.051
[ Tires Screech ]
Oh, dear.

18:39.118 --> 18:41.188
[ Gerbil Squeaking ]

18:41.254 --> 18:45.625
[ Grunting ]

18:45.692 --> 18:49.196
Your father's blood sugar
must be low again.
Carl, eat an orange!

18:49.262 --> 18:51.331
- Eat an orange!
- [ Groans ]

18:51.398 --> 18:55.868
Dad! Okay. Okay, I'll do it.
I'll go back.

18:55.935 --> 18:59.772
Just stop throwin' the gerbils.
My hands are full, and they pee
when they're scared.

18:59.839 --> 19:02.375
- You promise you'll go back?
- I'll go back.

19:02.442 --> 19:04.977
Good. I'm gonna
hold onto Squiggy...

19:05.044 --> 19:06.913
in case you change
your mind.

19:06.979 --> 19:11.083
- [ Car Door Closes ]
- I wanna play! Dad, hit me!
I'm open!

19:11.150 --> 19:15.121
[ Earl Narrating ] So I went
back to my cheatin' wife
and two "igellitimate" kids.

19:15.188 --> 19:19.526
What can I say?
Love those damn gerbils.

19:19.592 --> 19:24.631
And even though I stayed married
for possibly the craziest reason
anyone has ever stayed married,

19:24.697 --> 19:28.468
it didn't take me long
to realize what my dad
was talkin' about.

19:28.535 --> 19:32.372
* Together we learn
to read and write *

19:32.439 --> 19:34.774
* A child is black *

19:34.841 --> 19:36.909
* A child is white *
These people did need me.

19:36.976 --> 19:41.548
* The whole world looks
upon the sight *

19:41.614 --> 19:44.384
I wasn't the best dad,
but at least I was a dad.

19:44.451 --> 19:46.519
* A beautiful sight *

19:46.586 --> 19:49.389
Earl Junior's real dad hadn't
forgotten about him either.

19:49.456 --> 19:52.392
And eventually Joy fell back
into the arms of Darnell...

19:52.459 --> 19:55.295
'cause, well, that's where
her heart wanted to be.

19:55.362 --> 19:57.630
** [ Continues ]

20:01.701 --> 20:04.437
And when Darnell
was finally ready to be
a husband and a father,

20:04.504 --> 20:07.307
Joy and the kids
didn't need me anymore.

20:07.374 --> 20:09.809
But when they did need me,
I was there.

20:09.876 --> 20:12.812
It was the only good thing
I ever did before I made
the list.

20:12.879 --> 20:16.416
And I owe it all to my dad
for not lettin' me give up.

20:16.483 --> 20:20.720
* Together they grow
to see the light *

20:20.787 --> 20:25.024
* To see the light *
Check it out, Dad.
It's got a cord.

20:25.091 --> 20:27.994
* The world is black *

20:28.060 --> 20:30.196
* The world is white *

20:30.263 --> 20:32.332
* It turns by day *

20:32.399 --> 20:35.535
* And then by night *
That sure is a nice lamp
your boy made, isn't it?

20:35.602 --> 20:38.371
* A child is black
A child is white *

20:38.438 --> 20:41.274
Yeah, it sure is.
* Together they grow *

20:41.341 --> 20:44.176
* To see the light *

20:44.243 --> 20:49.148
* To see the light **

20:49.215 --> 20:52.985
[ Gasping, Screaming ]
